      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEA SALT (9) was in the money when resuming two starts ago then scored a commanding win last start over 1800m at this track, getting home by 16 metres after taking an early lead. Finds a nice race and will prove very tough to beat once more. LAST TANGO IN HEAVEN NZ (7) finished eighth last start over 2230m here, beaten 21 metres, after a good third at Port Pirie the run prior. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but finds a suitable assignment and can make amends. DEUCE COUPE NZ (3) found form and scored two runs back then came back to earth when he broke and finished seventh last start over 1800m at this circuit, coming home 7 metres from the winner. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Beautifully placed and is able to make amends. TONKAWAIKON (1) could only finish sixth over 1800m at this course most recently. Open to improvement and is in the mix for some minor money.",
